{"id":"280590838_New_Criteria_for_MRD_and_Gabidulin_Codes_and_some_Rank-Metric_Code_Constructions","abstract":"In this work we present a new criterion to check if a given rank-metric code\nis a maximum rank distance (MRD) code. Moreover, we derive a criterion to check\nif a given rank-metric code is a generalized Gabidulin code. We then use these\nresults to come up with constructions of linear MRD codes of length 4 and\ndimension 2 that are not generalized Gabidulin codes.","authors":["Anna-Lena Horlemann-Trautmann","Kyle Marshall"],"meta":["July 2015Advances in Mathematics of Communications 11(3)","DOI:10.3934/amc.2017042","SourcearXiv"],"references":["283531644_Extension_of_Overbeck's_Attack_for_Gabidulin_Based_Cryptosystems","274730556_A_new_family_of_linear_maximum_rank_distance_codes","235008632_Theory_of_codes_with_maximum_rank_distance_translation","224621743_The_new_construction_of_rank_codes","282831084_Non-linear_maximum_rank_distance_codes","270066303_Introduction_to_Finite_Fields_and_Their_Applications","258819223_Equivalence_for_Rank-Metric_and_Matrix_Codes_and_Automorphism_Groups_of_Gabidulin_Codes","242354643_Introduction_to_finite_fields_and_their_applications_rev_ed","220074347_Bilinear_Forms_over_a_Finite_Field_with_Applications_to_Coding_Theory","3084882_Isometries_for_Rank_Distance_and_Permutation_Group_of_Gabidulin_Codes"]}